tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE printing_materials_inventory (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  material_name STRING,
  material_type STRING,
  remaining_quantity INT
)

CREATE TABLE filaments (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  material_name VARCHAR(255),
  color VARCHAR(50),
  diameter FLOAT,
  length FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE resins (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  material_name VARCHAR(255),
  color VARCHAR(50),
  type VARCHAR(50),
  volume FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE filaments (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    quantity INT NOT NULL,
    color VARCHAR(50),
    material VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE resins (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    quantity INT NOT NULL,
    color VARCHAR(50),
    type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE print_jobs (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    filament_id INT,
    resin_id INT,
    printer_id INT,
    quantity INT NOT NULL,
    start_time TIMESTAMP,
    end_time TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE filaments (
    filament_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    filament_name VARCHAR(255),
    filament_type VARCHAR(100),
    filament_color VARCHAR(50),
    filament_price DECIMAL(10, 2)
)

CREATE TABLE resins (
    resin_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    resin_name VARCHAR(255),
    resin_type VARCHAR(100),
    resin_color VARCHAR(50),
    resin_price DECIMAL(10, 2)
)

CREATE TABLE inventory (
    inventory_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    material_id INT,
    quantity INT
)

CREATE TABLE material_types (
    material_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    material_name VARCHAR(255)
)

CREATE TABLE supplier (
    supplier_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    supplier_name VARCHAR(255),
    supplier_location VARCHAR(100)
)
